01:19:21.290 --> 01:19:22.916
I got a tiny head?

01:19:27.088 --> 01:19:28.338
Zalinsky.

01:19:32.760 --> 01:19:34.094
Say something.

01:19:37.973 --> 01:19:41.768
Mr. Zalinsky? I'm Tommy Callahan,
Big Tom Callahan's son.

01:19:42.812 --> 01:19:45.647
Sorry to hear about your dad.
He was a good man.

01:19:48.484 --> 01:19:50.860
Went a little heavy
on the pine-tree perfume there, kid.

01:19:51.612 --> 01:19:53.738
Sir, it's a taxi-cab air freshener.

01:19:53.823 --> 01:19:57.075
Great, you've pinpointed it.
Step two is washing it off.

01:19:58.244 --> 01:20:00.161
Sir, what exactly happened here?

01:20:00.246 --> 01:20:01.996
He came out of the shadows behind me.

01:20:02.081 --> 01:20:05.291
And after he hit me many times
in the head with a hammer,

01:20:05.376 --> 01:20:08.044
I had to give him my gun.
You know, I've got kids.

01:20:08.129 --> 01:20:10.922
So, as more details emerge
on this attempted bank robbery

01:20:11.006 --> 01:20:12.799
Action 8 will be there.

01:20:13.843 --> 01:20:16.928
But the Callahan factory
has been in my family for 70 years,

01:20:17.012 --> 01:20:18.596
you can't just shut it down.

01:20:18.681 --> 01:20:20.640
You got to look at it
from my point of view.

01:20:20.724 --> 01:20:23.476
Callahan's a premium name.
That's what I'm buying.

01:20:23.561 --> 01:20:26.521
I can make the parts in one of my
factories, put them in a Callahan box

01:20:26.605 --> 01:20:28.606
and sell them in my stores
at a premium price.

01:20:28.691 --> 01:20:31.651
Why keep your factory going
when all I want is the goddamn box?

01:20:31.735 --> 01:20:34.362
I'll tell you why.
Because there's a town involved here.

01:20:34.447 --> 01:20:37.198
Callahan factory is the only thing
keeping it alive.

01:20:37.283 --> 01:20:40.285
Believe it or not, I'm providing a service.
I'm thinning the corporate herd.

01:20:40.369 --> 01:20:42.996
You've seen Daktari,
the weaker animals always go.

01:20:43.080 --> 01:20:45.874
Sure the kids cry when you tie old Tiger
to a tree and shoot him.

01:20:45.958 --> 01:20:48.126
But that's life.
America's in a state of renewal.

01:20:48.210 --> 01:20:50.879
We gotta have the strength
to tie a few factories to a tree

01:20:50.963 --> 01:20:52.297
and bash them with a shovel.

01:20:52.381 --> 01:20:54.507
Meanwhile, if I can grab your share
of the market,

01:20:54.592 --> 01:20:56.968
put a little coin in my pocket
by being the asshole,

01:20:57.052 --> 01:20:59.053
well, what the hell? Know what I mean?

01:20:59.221 --> 01:21:01.973
Boy, you sure are different
in your TV commercials.

01:21:02.057 --> 01:21:04.392
What the American public
doesn't know

01:21:04.477 --> 01:21:06.186
is what makes them
the American public.

01:21:06.270 --> 01:21:07.562
All right?

01:21:10.900 --> 01:21:11.941
God, I love that.

01:21:12.026 --> 01:21:13.776
Hell, folks believe me when I tell them

01:21:13.861 --> 01:21:15.987
we're not just building
automotive components here,

01:21:16.071 --> 01:21:18.698
we're adding horsepower
to American industry.

01:21:24.747 --> 01:21:27.874
You say one word to anyone and I will
kill you, do you understand me?

01:21:27.958 --> 01:21:29.501
It looks real.

01:21:33.297 --> 01:21:35.673
Yeah, television's been
good to me, son.

01:21:35.799 --> 01:21:38.551
"I make car parts
for the American working man

01:21:38.636 --> 01:21:41.638
"because that's what I am,
and that's who I care about."

01:21:43.349 --> 01:21:46.351
The truth is, I make car parts
for the American working man

01:21:46.435 --> 01:21:49.270
because I'm a hell of a salesman,
and he doesn't know any better.

01:21:49.355 --> 01:21:52.482
Son, since you're no longer
a shareholder, this is where I leave you.

01:21:52.566 --> 01:21:55.735
Don't feel bad. This chain of events
was set in motion a long time ago.

01:21:55.819 --> 01:21:58.530
You and your bald-headed friend did
what you could, that's commendable.

01:21:58.614 --> 01:22:00.907
Marty, have Security see these boys out.

01:22:01.617 --> 01:22:03.701
- Mrs. Callahan.
- Sir.

01:22:03.786 --> 01:22:05.620
I trust your trip went well.

01:22:06.705 --> 01:22:08.873
What's my family doing in there?

01:22:19.552 --> 01:22:21.344
I thought they were on my side.

01:22:21.428 --> 01:22:24.264
They had a lot to gain
if the factory was sold.

01:22:24.765 --> 01:22:26.432
Boy, did I screw up.

01:22:26.725 --> 01:22:30.228
My so-called family deserted me.
Michelle's mad at me.

01:22:30.312 --> 01:22:33.898
I lost the factory. The town's
going under, and I'm out of a job.

01:22:36.318 --> 01:22:39.153
Could have done without that.
Jeez! I'm an idiot!

01:22:41.740 --> 01:22:45.910
- Boy, I sure let my dad down.
- You tried as hard as you could.

01:22:46.120 --> 01:22:48.997
When we first started out,
I thought you'd just walk through this

01:22:49.081 --> 01:22:51.708
like you walk through everything else.
But you didn't.

01:22:51.834 --> 01:22:54.210
Your dad would have been proud of you.

01:22:55.045 --> 01:22:56.546
And you got a friend out of it.

01:22:56.630 --> 01:23:00.008
Now, I know it doesn't matter,
because you have so many, but

01:23:00.759 --> 01:23:02.051
I don't.

01:23:04.888 --> 01:23:06.222
Thanks, man.

01:23:08.684 --> 01:23:10.018
Tommy!

01:23:11.562 --> 01:23:12.729
Michelle!

01:23:12.813 --> 01:23:14.939
- Don't tell her about my hair.
- Let it go.

01:23:15.024 --> 01:23:16.941
God, I was worried I wouldn't find you.

01:23:17.026 --> 01:23:19.152
- What are you doing here?
- I got your message.

01:23:19.236 --> 01:23:21.487
Okay, I was at the airport.
I was going home

01:23:21.572 --> 01:23:24.949
and I saw your stepbrother and your
stepmother and he was kissing her.

01:23:25.034 --> 01:23:26.701
- So?
- With his tongue.

01:23:27.703 --> 01:23:30.455
- He's doing his mommy?
- She's not his mom. They're married.

01:23:30.539 --> 01:23:32.457
They were lying to your dad
the whole time.

01:23:32.541 --> 01:23:34.667
My brother got his police report. See?

01:23:34.752 --> 01:23:37.587
- They lied to my dad?
- They're con artists. They suckered him.

01:23:37.671 --> 01:23:39.297
They lied to my dad.

01:23:48.515 --> 01:23:52.602
Richard, I'm gonna need your watch.
I've got a plan.

01:23:52.686 --> 01:23:53.895
Yikes!

01:24:04.031 --> 01:24:06.658
Folks, Mr. Zalinsky gave us
specific instructions

01:24:06.742 --> 01:24:08.326
to bar you from the building.

01:24:08.410 --> 01:24:11.120
Sorry, boys.
Hopefully, we'll just be in and out.

01:24:11.246 --> 01:24:13.623
- My God, he's wired.
- And no cops.

01:24:13.707 --> 01:24:15.750
Wouldn't want things to get messy.

01:24:20.798 --> 01:24:22.548
- That was fun.
- Now what?

01:24:22.633 --> 01:24:25.426
Well, it's 6:00. Time for the news.

01:24:27.221 --> 01:24:29.055
Excuse me! Miss?

01:24:29.473 --> 01:24:30.598
Oh, God.

01:24:34.186 --> 01:24:35.561
Done this before?

01:24:36.522 --> 01:24:38.022
Thank you, Marty.

01:24:43.946 --> 01:24:46.114
My, your hands move quickly.

01:24:46.615 --> 01:24:49.534
Only when I see something I want,
Mrs. Callahan.

01:24:50.953 --> 01:24:52.537
It just doesn't seem right.

01:24:53.288 --> 01:24:54.831
Hi! Got a second?

01:24:54.957 --> 01:24:57.583
- What the hell's going on here?
- Oh, my God. We're gonna die.

01:24:57.668 --> 01:25:00.628
- Tommy, what are you doing?
- Hi, Ted. Hi, Frank. Excuse me, Marty.

01:25:00.754 --> 01:25:01.879
Okay, we're live.

01:25:01.964 --> 01:25:05.383
We now switch live to our reporter
who is at the scene with the bomber.

01:25:05.467 --> 01:25:06.968
This is Nicole Taylor
in downtown Chicago.

01:25:07.052 --> 01:25:08.136
Look, it's Tommy!

01:25:08.220 --> 01:25:11.180
...who says he strapped a bomb...
- Nicole, I've got something to say.

01:25:11.306 --> 01:25:12.807
Please. May I?

01:25:13.684 --> 01:25:16.310
Hi, this is Tommy Callahan here
with Mr. Ray Zalinsky

01:25:16.395 --> 01:25:17.895
American Auto Parts King.

01:25:17.980 --> 01:25:20.606
Honey, look at this human bomb
on the news.

01:25:21.817 --> 01:25:25.403
Yeah, I buy brake pads off him.
I thought we were watching cartoons.

01:25:26.864 --> 01:25:29.782
Mr. Zalinsky, for years
you've been putting ads on TV.

01:25:29.867 --> 01:25:34.620
And they always end up with you saying,
"I make car parts for..."

01:25:34.830 --> 01:25:36.289
How does it go?

01:25:37.332 --> 01:25:40.585
I make car parts
for the American working man

01:25:40.669 --> 01:25:43.671
because that's what I am
and that's who I care about.

01:25:43.797 --> 01:25:47.383
And that's why I'm here, Ray.
You see, back in Sandusky, Ohio,

01:25:47.468 --> 01:25:49.969
there are 300 American workers
at Callahan Auto.

01:25:50.053 --> 01:25:52.305
We make the best parts money can buy.

01:25:52.389 --> 01:25:55.099
Right now those workers
are in danger of losing their jobs.

01:25:55.184 --> 01:25:57.477
They're praying somebody's gonna
step up and help them.

01:25:57.561 --> 01:25:59.645
Is that why you
strapped a bomb to your chest?

01:25:59.730 --> 01:26:01.856
This isn't a bomb.
These are road flares.

01:26:02.274 --> 01:26:05.443
Road flares? Did you live under
power lines as a kid or something?

01:26:05.944 --> 01:26:06.986
Why?

01:26:07.070 --> 01:26:09.614
You guys want this
or American Gladiators?

01:26:10.073 --> 01:26:11.240
Gladiators.

01:26:11.366 --> 01:26:14.535
So, do you think Zalinsky Industries
can help these folks?

01:26:14.787 --> 01:26:16.704
I'll be happy to look into it.

01:26:17.206 --> 01:26:19.749
I'll tell you what.
I can get a good look at a T-bone

01:26:19.875 --> 01:26:21.459
by sticking my head up a bull's ass

01:26:21.543 --> 01:26:24.170
but I'd rather take
the butcher's word for it.

01:26:25.297 --> 01:26:28.382
Am I just severely wasted
or does Tommy look bloated?

01:26:28.467 --> 01:26:32.386
No, it's TV, man.
Camera adds a couple hundred pounds.

01:26:33.305 --> 01:26:35.431
Ray, we're not looking
for a handout here.

01:26:35.557 --> 01:26:37.183
I'm offering you a great deal.

01:26:37.726 --> 01:26:40.353
This is an order for half a million
Callahan brake pads

01:26:40.437 --> 01:26:41.729
to be sold in your stores

01:26:41.814 --> 01:26:45.691
made by the American working man
for the American working man.

01:26:49.863 --> 01:26:51.823
Well, absolutely.

01:26:51.907 --> 01:26:54.826
It would be my great pleasure.
I mean, what have I got to lose?

01:26:54.910 --> 01:26:56.744
A great American product, right?

01:26:56.829 --> 01:26:59.997
I don't believe it. Tommy just sold
half a million brake pads.

01:27:00.123 --> 01:27:04.168
Tommy just sold
a half a million brake pads!

01:27:04.253 --> 01:27:05.253
Yeah!

01:27:10.342 --> 01:27:11.634
What difference does it make?

01:27:11.718 --> 01:27:14.428
The company's gonna be mine
in 10 minutes anyway, right?

01:27:15.931 --> 01:27:17.974
Mr. Zalinsky, thank you.

01:27:18.058 --> 01:27:19.934
Thank you, Tommy Boy. And thank you.

01:27:20.018 --> 01:27:23.688
And remember, you can pick up these
great brake pads from Callahan Auto

01:27:23.772 --> 01:27:27.441
at all my Zalinsky Auto Parts outlets
all over North America.

01:27:27.568 --> 01:27:28.943
Go, Tommy!

01:27:29.027 --> 01:27:30.945
For the moment it looks like a tragedy

01:27:31.071 --> 01:27:33.364
has been averted
and a town has been saved.

01:27:33.448 --> 01:27:36.576
For Action News, I'm Nicole Taylor,
reporting live.

01:27:36.952 --> 01:27:38.953
Okay. We're out of here.

01:27:39.288 --> 01:27:41.998
Wait a minute, fat boy.
You lost your shares to the bank.

01:27:42.082 --> 01:27:44.000
You don't even have a right to be here.

01:27:44.126 --> 01:27:45.960
Gee, funny you should bring that up.

01:27:46.044 --> 01:27:48.754
'Cause I'm not sure
that you have the right to be here.

01:27:48.839 --> 01:27:50.673
What have we got here?

01:27:50.757 --> 01:27:53.676
- My God, it's a police report.
- Now what's all this about?

01:27:53.760 --> 01:27:56.721
Let's see.
Paul Barrish, married, May, 1993

01:27:56.805 --> 01:27:59.056
to Beverly Barrish, a.k.a. Beverly Burns.

01:27:59.141 --> 01:28:02.977
Richard, how could Beverly be married
to Paul and my dad at the same time?

01:28:03.061 --> 01:28:05.104
- Interesting.
- Yes. Provocative.

01:28:05.480 --> 01:28:09.066
What I think it means is your marriage
to my dad was never legal.

01:28:09.151 --> 01:28:11.736
Which also means that Beverly's shares
still belong to Tommy.

01:28:11.820 --> 01:28:14.697
- Isn't that right, Mr. Rittenhauer?
- Yes. I believe that's right.

01:28:14.781 --> 01:28:16.198
- Mr. Reilly?
- I'd say that's right.

01:28:16.283 --> 01:28:18.034
- Mr. Gilmore?
- Absolutely.

01:28:18.535 --> 01:28:19.785
And let me guess.

01:28:19.870 --> 01:28:22.246
You're not going to be selling me
the company now.

01:28:22.331 --> 01:28:25.124
- Are you, Tommy Boy?
- No, sir.

01:28:25.208 --> 01:28:27.627
Ray, I have no idea
what they're talking about.

01:28:27.711 --> 01:28:30.254
That's it. I'm not going to take this.

01:28:30.339 --> 01:28:32.882
- It's not over yet, Lee Harvey.
- Let's see.

01:28:33.342 --> 01:28:36.344
Warrants outstanding:
New Mexico, mail fraud

01:28:36.428 --> 01:28:38.262
Colorado, wire fraud

01:28:38.347 --> 01:28:41.933
and coming soon to Ohio,
computer fraud.

01:28:45.145 --> 01:28:46.228
Get him!

01:28:46.313 --> 01:28:48.356
Don't let him leave the complex, Marty.

01:28:52.861 --> 01:28:56.864
- Hey, you forgot your wife.
- Screw you. Screw all of you!

01:28:58.617 --> 01:29:00.701
Crash test in progress.

01:29:02.663 --> 01:29:05.039
- Not good.
- Hit the brakes.

01:29:19.554 --> 01:29:21.222
That will ruin his weekend.

01:29:21.306 --> 01:29:23.057
Well, kid, you threw one by me.

01:29:23.141 --> 01:29:25.768
Savor the flavor because it sure as hell
won't happen again.

01:29:25.852 --> 01:29:28.270
- In the meantime, good luck to you.
- Thank you, sir.

01:29:28.397 --> 01:29:30.898
Marty, cut a check to Callahan Auto
for those brake pads.

01:29:30.983 --> 01:29:32.441
- Yes, sir.
- And you,

01:29:32.526 --> 01:29:35.069
with all this excitement here,
I kind of got a little hungry.

01:29:35.153 --> 01:29:38.072
Want to step over to my club
and we'll grab something to eat?

01:29:41.451 --> 01:29:43.494
- Thank you. I'd like that.
- Good.

01:29:43.578 --> 01:29:45.871
Marty, find out where the police
will be taking him.

01:29:45.956 --> 01:29:48.207
Send over a bottle of bubbly
with a bucket of ice and a card.

01:29:48.291 --> 01:29:50.042
Have it say, "Tough break.
Get drunk on me.

01:29:50.127 --> 01:29:52.920
"Use the bucket to ice down
your marbles. Yours, Z."

01:29:53.130 --> 01:29:57.008
Well, Mr. Callahan,
looks like we're back in business.

01:29:57.092 --> 01:29:58.634
Yes, sir, Mr. Rittenhauer.

01:29:58.719 --> 01:30:00.177
- That's great, Tommy.
- Great, Tommy.

01:30:00.262 --> 01:30:01.470
Thanks.

01:30:02.055 --> 01:30:04.140
Way to go, Tommy Callahan.

01:30:11.106 --> 01:30:14.775
- That was pathetic.
- Shut up, Richard.

01:30:17.237 --> 01:30:19.447
This is a very proud day for me.

01:30:19.781 --> 01:30:24.160
I want to introduce you
to the new president of Callahan Auto,

01:30:24.453 --> 01:30:26.537
Tom Callahan, Jr.

01:30:33.086 --> 01:30:35.004
Tommy, will you say something?

01:30:40.552 --> 01:30:44.305
Ever since I was a kid, you people
have been like a family to me.

01:30:46.224 --> 01:30:48.684
Louis, we built our first fort together.

01:30:48.977 --> 01:30:52.563
And, Danny, remember when we used
to burn ants with a magnifying glass?

01:30:54.566 --> 01:30:58.652
R.T., I lost my virginity to your daughter,
for crying out loud.

01:31:00.864 --> 01:31:02.656
Rob, you were there.

01:31:03.825 --> 01:31:07.828
Anyway, I just want you to know
that as long as I'm around

01:31:07.913 --> 01:31:09.455
I'm gonna bust my butt

01:31:09.539 --> 01:31:11.373
and make sure that
every last one of you

01:31:11.458 --> 01:31:14.001
always has a job right here at Callahan.

01:31:42.322 --> 01:31:44.949
Dad, I got a little problem here.

01:31:45.408 --> 01:31:47.952
I've been stuck out here for an hour
with no wind again

01:31:48.036 --> 01:31:50.538
and I'm supposed to be at Michelle's
for dinner.

01:31:51.248 --> 01:31:54.250
So if you could give me a little help
I'd appreciate it.

01:31:54.417 --> 01:31:56.377
If not, don't worry about it.

01:31:58.880 --> 01:32:01.674
I'm trying to do everything
I think you'd be doing

01:32:01.800 --> 01:32:04.093
and so far it's going pretty good.

01:32:04.469 --> 01:32:07.513
I just want to tell you
that I still love you and

01:32:09.224 --> 01:32:10.933
I sure miss you a lot.

01:32:29.077 --> 01:32:30.578
Thanks, Dad.

01:32:32.330 --> 01:32:34.498
Son of a... That's gonna leave a mark.

